items.name: serialkiller
items.description: Small tool for typing automation, of all serials you may have to insert anywere. Smart and useful for people working on computer maintenance.

items.name: eyequery
items.description: Eyequery is intended to be a graphical database query authoring tool, allowing  non-technical business-users to query useful information without the help from  developers.

items.name: LazyLibrary
items.description: A Java Library Implementing Features I use or would find useful at some point. {Compile .java Files to Use Library OR DL Pre-Compiled JAR}

items.name: java-http-server
items.description: This very leight webserver is useful if you want to easily expose a filesystem path over HTTP (http://www.jibble.org/miniwebserver/) . Useful for a local maven repository specified in the pom.xml, when you don't want to change settings.xml file.

items.name: ant-jira
items.description: Ant task for Jira integration. Useful for things like automating quality metrics, e.g. bugs/1K lines of code or creating Jira issues right from the build.

items.name: bean-loader
items.description: A database loader that automagically injects the results of prepared statements into Java beans (without any configuration), returning them in a variety of useful & exciting ways.

items.name: java-dependency-unifier
items.description: Given two similar dependencies, bytecode manipulate each so that they look like the other (throwing UnsupportedOperationException's where they differ). This is useful for two teams working on trunk based development, but they have different versions of libraries depended upon.

items.name: ColorPicker-Android
items.description: This libary provides a wheel color picker for Android developers. It is very useful when you develope an App with requirements of picking color. This libary is based on 2012 Lars Werkman HoloColorPicker Library.

items.name: Aligma
items.description: "Aligma" is a miniature relational database management system for storing data. It can be very useful for educational institutions to keep and access a huge amount of information regarding students, their participation, grades and classes.

items.name: Algorithms
items.description: This repository contains many useful algorithms which can be used to solve day to day problems. These algorithms are written in Java language and can be tweaked a little to implement in commercial applications.

items.name: storage-manager
items.description: An android app that can mount/format a partition(fat32, ntfs, ext) or change a device's partition table. It'll be useful in mount your usb otg devices.

items.name: J2ME-FlashLight
items.description: My "Hello World" project to start learning J2ME. Might be useful. It is a "flashlight" for J2ME phones. When you start the app, it turns all your screen white.

items.name: UtilityMobs
items.description: Adds new, simple utility mobs similar to the vanilla snow and iron golems. In addition to the normal golems, it also adds simple turret golems and the ever-useful block golems!

items.name: GradleVariables
items.description: Sample application shows how to write variables and methods in build.gradle file and later access it in activity class. Very useful if you are developing your application based on build variants.

items.name: TwitFrame
items.description: An Android application that allows you to turn your device into a frame that streams your friends Twitter statuses. Useful for when you dock your phone and want to passively watch your statuses.

items.name: multithreaded_downloader
items.description: A for-fun and also useful project. A command-line multi-threaded downloader in Java, given the url and output file name, download the resource. The concurrent level could also be set

items.name: ImageSplitter
items.description: Splits 16 bit per channel image into two 8 bit per channel image (lower 8 bits and upper 8 bits). Useful wehen working staff like webgl and wants use 16 bit per channel.

items.name: gvoa
items.description: For learning english, I tried many VOA related applications, but none of them is easy to use. So I decided to write one for myself.  The UI will be very simple, but the content will be very useful.

items.name: DevHub
items.description: DevHub Android App is a Material Design App to learn thought video-tutorials about the most famous languages for programming. The videos are in Spanish, but the app supports English too. The most useful functionalities are implemented like Login, User session, Profile, Settings, Tabs, Consume data from API, Rendered video from YouTube API...

items.name: ImgC
items.description: Ment for generating wallpapers for multiscreen desktops. Identifies and merges different files based on their name (e.g. Image_0.jpg + Image_1.jpg + Image_2.jpg = Image.jpg). Also reverses order on images (useful when primary desktop is the right instead of left).

items.name: RangeWalker
items.description: A simple GPS application for android that lets you mark your current location, and then subsequently mark a second location to get calculated straightline distance between the two geo location (in yards).  Might be useful for a golfer who wants to know the distances he/she is hitting his clubs.

items.name: CImageCache
items.description: This library can download images from URL and save them inside your external storage. If device does not have external storage it takes device cache directory to store images downloaded from the URL provided. Library used Asyn to download images and they want show in gallery. Mostly useful if apps need to cache images from url tile images changed.

items.name: MagicSort
items.description: MagicSort is a Java library used for sorting any object array by using iterative quick sort and selection sort when the array size is small. Moreover, it provides some useful built-in comparators for sorting strings and files. It can sort files by file types, but when the file types are the same, sort them by their file names.

items.name: ik_toolset
items.description: A set of tools for analyzing graphs.  The tools were designed to aid in the classification of a graph with respect to the property of intrinsic knotting.  This being said, other useful graph related tools were created in order to achieve these ends.

items.name: neural-network-pruning
items.description: A web application using the neural network pruning algorithm developed by Henrik Saxén and Frank Petterson. The purpose of the application is to use measured from any system and identify which of the measurements that are useful to describe the state of the system.

items.name: hudson-flashlog-plugin
items.description: Hudson plugin which allows you to capture the flash logs during a build. This is useful to debug unit tests or integration tests. NOTE: currently tested under CENT OS / OS X. Windows integration is ready but is not tested at the moment. Will post updates when tested.

items.name: material-two-stage-rating
items.description: A library, following Google's Material Design, to help you promote your Android app by prompting users to rate the app after using it for a few days. Its two stage process ensures higher reviews to go to playstore while getting useful feedback on lower ratings.

items.name: BigflagJavaDevPlugin4Eclipse
items.description: This is a java dev plugin 4 Eclipse for my team. The aim of this tool is to make the java dev quickly, easily and standardly for my team in the help of Eclipse plug-in. Hope it is also useful for any other java developers who is using Eclipse.

items.name: AndroidAppClasses
items.description: This repo contains useful android classes have used for some projects and still using. In the classes there are helpful functions and methods that can be later used in the activity classes by just calling them to make your task work well and better concerning Strings, Integers, Bitmaps, Sharedpreference, SQLite database and others.

items.name: T2Util
items.description: Very easy-to-use object-oriented Java API for connecting to the mass spectrometer remotely and extracting monoisotopic peak lists. Useful if want to make an application that extracts the peak lists directly from the instrument instead of having to download the files manually.
